    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent. | Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Ap 24. 76</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>You are the most wonderful man for accuracy, &amp; I for blundering.— I wrote to R. Geographical Soc<hi rend="superscript">y</hi>. &amp; I enclose titles which answer 4 of your questions.<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>All the cases in which I refer to charts on a large scale &amp;c no doubt refer to originals which I had before me when I wrote.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>There are only a few other points to mention, but let me thank you sincerely for so many errata.</p>
<p>p. 219 l. 10 for <hi rend="underline">B de Candelaria</hi>, no doubt read <hi rend="underline">R</hi>. (Recif) <hi rend="underline">de Candelaria</hi>.<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>p. 233 l.5 for this island read as you say “these islands.”<ref target="#foot.f4"/></p>
<p>p. 239 last l. for northern end of <hi rend="underline">P</hi>alawan read southern.<ref target="#foot.f5"/></p>
<p>N.B p. 212 add to end of account of Rotoumah.</p>
<p>“D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. L. Forbes says (Two years in Fiji 1875 p. 229) that there is an extinct crater on this island.”<ref target="#foot.f6"/></p>
<p>It is very true every copy of Volcanic Is<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> &amp; S. America was sold. I am having London searched for second-hand copies. I think I gave my Brother copies, &amp; as he won’t care about them I have asked him (if he has them) to send them to you by Post.<ref target="#foot.f7"/></p>
<p>Smith &amp; Elder now wish to bring out a new Edit. of the 2 vols, in England; but this will make no difference to you, as I am firmly resolved not even to look at a single proof.—<ref target="#foot.f8"/></p>
<p>My dear Sir | Yours very sincerely | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">1.1 wrote] ‘o’ <hi rend="italic">over</hi> ‘i’ </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n2">2.1 originals 2.2] <hi rend="italic">after del</hi> ‘the’ </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n3">5.1 l.5] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi> </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n4">6.1 northern] <hi rend="italic">above del</hi> ‘southern’ </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n5">6.1 southern] <hi rend="italic">above del</hi> ‘northern’ </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n6">10.1 now] <hi rend="italic">above del</hi> ‘also’ </note>
            </div>

            
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
